    "body": "## Requirements\r\n\r\n1. Enable the usage of a `genesis_time` property in a given `truffle-config.js`.\r\n\r\nExample:\r\n```\r\nmodule.exports = {\r\n  networks: {\r\n    development: {\r\n      host: \"127.0.0.1\",\r\n      port: 8545,\r\n      genesis_time: \"2019-04-09T02:10:14Z\",\r\n      network_id: \"*\"\r\n    }\r\n  }\r\n};\r\n```\r\n\r\n2. Throw a helpful `Error` if `genesis_time` is *not* passed a valid `Date`.\r\n3. Ensure that the valid `genesis_time` value is passed as a configurable option internally within truffle before starting a default `ganache-core` chain for `truffle test`.\r\n4. Add an integration mocha test to proper functionality (proper behavior when passed a valid `Date` and proper error handling when passed an invalid `Date`).\r\n\r\n## Prerequisite Context\r\n\r\n- Familiarity with the options `ganache-core` is expecting on its side for setting a genesis block time: https://github.com/trufflesuite/ganache-core#options\r\n- Familiarity with the entry point for `truffle test`: https://github.com/trufflesuite/truffle/blob/develop/packages/truffle-core/lib/commands/test.js, specifically [these lines](https://github.com/trufflesuite/truffle/blob/develop/packages/truffle-core/lib/commands/test.js#L147-L167).\r\n- Familiarity with the script for spinning up the default `ganache-core` in testing: https://github.com/trufflesuite/truffle/blob/develop/packages/truffle-environment/chain.js\r\n- Possibly familiarity with the chain environment file for error handling (might be better handled earlier in the `truffle test` sequence): https://github.com/trufflesuite/truffle/blob/develop/packages/truffle-environment/environment.js\r\n- Familiarity with current `truffle test` integration tests, i.e. https://github.com/trufflesuite/truffle/blob/develop/packages/truffle/test/scenarios/happy_path/happypath.js, particularly [these lines](https://github.com/trufflesuite/truffle/blob/develop/packages/truffle/test/scenarios/happy_path/happypath.js#L113-L125).",
